'''psychrometer'''
# A form of [[hygrometer]]. The psychrometer has a [[sling]] attached to the mounted bulb thermometers with a [[handle]] on the free end of the sling with which an operator can whirl the bulb thermometers in a circular pattern and speed up the [[evaporation]] of water from the wet bulb thermometer. The difference between the two readings constitutes the measure of the dryness of the air-or [[humidity]] of the atmosphere-at your location.

